Basically the following is an excerpt from [`res.sendfile()`](https://github.com/visionmedia/express/blob/master/lib/response.js#L317) code:

```
res.sendfile = function(path, options, fn){
  ....
  // cleanup
  function cleanup() {
    req.socket.removeListener('error', error);
  }

  ...
  this.on('finish', cleanup);
};
```

When sending the file is done, it calls `finish` which calls `cleanup`. That's all. Nobody calls `fn` callback. This causes a problem that the callee flow never ends. For instance, I use `async.waterfall`. In the last callback flow I send a file which should call its callback. Then the last error callback is called and the async flow is completed. Since `sendfile` never calls the callback, the main async flow never completes.

Ideally, it should:

```
this.on('finish', function () {
    cleanup();
    if (fn) fn();
});
```

